IST Authentication System
Educational Identity Provider with Budget Management

This project was developed as part of an academic assessment to demonstrate
modern authentication practices, secure coding principles, and comprehensive
full-stack development for educational technology solutions.

Developer: Manzi Niyongira Osee
Year: 2025
Institution: Institut Sup√©rieur de Technologie (IST)
Purpose: Academic Assessment - Identity Provider Development

The system includes:
- Centralized authentication and authorization
- Educational budget management and expense tracking
- Role-based access control for educational institutions
- Modern security practices and JWT token management
- OAuth integration and email verification systems

Built with modern technologies:
- Backend: Spring Boot 3.5.6 with Java 21
- Frontend: React 18.3.1 with TypeScript
- Database: H2 (in-memory for production deployment)
- Deployment: Fly.io (backend) and Vercel (frontend)

This software is provided for educational and demonstration purposes.
Commercial use is permitted under the MIT License terms above.